{
  "category": "Uncategorized",
  "description": "Fix Program Subpage Layout and Typography\n\nResolve UI rendering issues on program subpages (e.g., /pl/programs/sredniaki/) where visual elements are currently broken or improperly displayed.\n\nRequirements:\n- Audit all visual elements on program subpages to identify broken layouts\n- Fix CSS/styling issues causing UI destruction (misaligned elements, overflow, broken grids, etc.)\n- Ensure proper spacing and alignment of all page components\n- Verify typography hierarchy is correct (headings, body text, captions)\n- Apply consistent and pleasant font sizing, line height, and letter spacing\n- Ensure text is readable with appropriate contrast ratios\n- Test responsiveness across different screen sizes (mobile, tablet, desktop)\n- Verify consistency with other pages in the application\n- Test with actual program data to ensure dynamic content renders correctly\n- Cross-browser testing (Chrome, Firefox, Safari, Edge)\n\nElements to verify:\n- Page header and title section\n- Content blocks and text sections\n- Images and media elements\n- Buttons and interactive components\n- Navigation elements\n- Footer section\n\nSuccess criteria:\n- All page elements render in their intended positions\n- Typography is visually harmonious and easy to read\n- No visual artifacts, overlapping elements, or broken layouts\n- Consistent styling with the rest of the application",
